Genesis is a historical book and is regarded as literal history.
The geographical locations in connection with the story are historic.

The word "Genesis" means Origin or The Creation.

The Book of Genesis is divided into two sections:

	1. First section (chapters 1 to 11 ) => has God's patience been exhausted? Has god given up on the world?

The first section's focus is universal. It deals with the origin of the universe, the origin of mankind, the origin of sin, etc., and it tells how mankind came to be Alienated and separated from God and how sin perverted all of God's creation.

Genesis storypath:
Story of Adam and Eve, murder of Abel by his brother Cain
Story of Noah's Ark 
Story of the tower of Babel = different languages and nations

Genesis 12:3 
I will bless those who bless you, And I will curse him who curses you, And in shall all the families of the earth be blessed.

 the word "Families" derives from the Hebrew word 'Mishpakka', which means clans, tribes, and nation 

Exodus 19:3
3 Moses went up to the mountain of God. Then the LORD called to him from the mountain, saying: This is what you will say to the house of Jacob (nation of Israel); tell the Israelites: 4 You have seen how I treated the Egyptians and how I carried you up on eagles' wings and brought you to myself.
5 Now if you obey me fully and keep my covenant, then out of all nations you will be my own treasured from among all the people the Earth;  for all the earth  belongs to me, 6 you will be my kingdom of priests and a holy nation.’ These are the words you must give to the Israelites.



Four great events in the Book of Genesis :
	1. Creation
	2. Fall
	3. Noah's flood
	4. Tower of Babel 

Four great people in the Book of Genesis :
	1. Abraham
	2. Isaac
	3. Jacob
	4. Joseph.

God's plan from the beginning was to use one nation to reveal His plan of redemption to the rest of the world.
He revealed His plan of redemption to the Jews through what we refer to as the Old Testament.

Fulfilled the plan of redemption through Jesus Christ.

The Ultimate goal is to bring salvation to the entire world.

	• The Nine Basic Stages of the Old Testament :
	1. The creation stage: Genesis 1 to 11
	2. The patriarchal stage: Genesis 12 to 50
	3. The exodus stage
	4. The conquest stage
	5. The judges' stage
	6. The United Kingdom stage
	7. The divided kingdom stage
	8. The Babylonian captivity stage
	9. The return stage
